{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "sop", "internal": "shrinkwrap", "icon": "SOP/shrinkwrap", "since": "12.0", "tags": "reshape, normals, model", "version": "", "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Shrinkwrap"], "extent": [116, 131]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Takes the convex hull of input geometry and moves its polygons inwards along their normals."], "extent": [131, 231]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The Shrinkwrap operation computes the convex hull of the input geometry using\nthe same method as ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/tetrahedralize", "type": "link", "text": ["Tetrahedralize"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/tetrahedralize.html"}, ", and translates the\nresultant polygonal primitives inwards along their normals.\nUnlike the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/peak", "type": "link", "text": ["Peak SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/peak.html"}, ", which takes the point and moves it according\nto the average of the neighboring polygons, Shrinkwrap moves the polygons \nand recomputes their intersections, possibly creating new and removing old \npoints, but maintaining polygon normal directions. Polygons with more than\nthree edges are divided into triangles with the same normals as the original\npolygon."], "extent": [231, 844]}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [844, 856], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Distance"], "extent": [856, 866], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The translation distance inwards."], "extent": [892, 939]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/dist"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Clip Tolerance"], "extent": [939, 955], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The error tolerance for computing the new point positions."], "extent": [955, 1023]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Consolidate Tolerance"], "extent": [1023, 1046], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The error tolerance for fusing points together. This is equivalent to using consolidate points in the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/facet", "type": "link", "text": ["Facet SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/facet.html"}, "."], "extent": [1046, 1193]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1193, 1202], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/peak", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/peak.html"}], "extent": [1202, 1225]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["Shrinkwrap"], "summary": ["Takes the convex hull of input geometry and moves its polygons inwards along their normals."]}